You can buy soju, squid...

00:00:53.574 --> 00:00:54.074
No.

00:00:55.607 --> 00:00:57.607
I really like riding bikes.

00:01:05.220 --> 00:01:08.040
We are going to rent bikes with baskets. Yay!

00:01:09.060 --> 00:01:13.300
Yes. We must bring this back to get my ID card back. Now they have my ID card.

00:01:15.480 --> 00:01:17.053
Okay. Let's go.

00:01:17.053 --> 00:01:18.774
Wow!

00:01:18.774 --> 00:01:19.541
Let's go.

00:01:19.541 --> 00:01:20.041
Let's go.

00:01:20.620 --> 00:01:22.620
I'll follow.

00:01:24.060 --> 00:01:28.600
I'm riding a bike again after a really long time. I'm so happy!

00:01:33.080 --> 00:01:35.080
Seokjin is going slowly.

00:01:35.980 --> 00:01:37.980
Yes. In order to go with Kyung-hwa.

00:01:37.980 --> 00:01:38.555
Very good.

00:01:38.555 --> 00:01:40.340
I'm matching my speed to yours.

00:01:40.340 --> 00:01:41.174
Very considerate.

00:01:41.174 --> 00:01:42.915
Call me Mr. Jin Manners from now on.

00:01:43.454 --> 00:01:45.454
I'll watch you a little more (in the future).

00:01:47.215 --> 00:01:49.215
Just as I thought, since there aren't many people, it's very convenient to ride bikes.

00:01:49.215 --> 00:01:51.168
It's really good. The weather is nice, too.

00:01:53.660 --> 00:01:58.718
For real though, it's been a really long time since I've been to the Han River, and especially since I've ridden a bike by the Han River.

00:01:58.718 --> 00:02:00.460
When did you say was the last time you rode a bike?

00:02:00.800 --> 00:02:03.380
I guess maybe the last time I rode a bike by the Han River was when I was a university student.

00:02:03.480 --> 00:02:04.400
When you were a university student.

00:02:04.440 --> 00:02:04.940
Yes.

00:02:05.100 --> 00:02:07.380
Then about 20 years ago?

00:02:07.380 --> 00:02:08.120
What?!

00:02:08.120 --> 00:02:13.100
I used to ride a bike a lot in my neighborhood, both when I was little and after I grew up.

00:02:13.100 --> 00:02:15.100
In your neighborhood?

00:02:15.340 --> 00:02:17.500
Yes, I would start riding my bike in the neighborhood and then go far.

00:02:17.500 --> 00:02:28.100
Usually among guys, we would bring chicken and beer to the Han River and eat it here.

00:02:28.220 --> 00:02:29.180
Girls are the same.

00:02:29.340 --> 00:02:30.420
They are the same?

00:02:30.640 --> 00:02:34.660
There are some girls who bring pretty lunch boxes, 

00:02:34.954 --> 00:02:36.954
and there some who bring simple foods, 

00:02:37.440 --> 00:02:42.100
but as we age, I think more and more friends of mine know how to pack their own lunch box, 

00:02:42.360 --> 00:02:44.360
whereas when we were younger, we would always buy food.

00:02:45.460 --> 00:02:47.720
That's right. I assume many of them brought kimbap.

00:02:47.720 --> 00:02:50.600
No, unlike you expected, they didn't bring kimbap, 

00:02:50.600 --> 00:02:55.480
but sandwiches, or things like cheese, fruits like tomatoes, or something like that.

00:02:55.714 --> 00:02:56.960
Sounds like the lunch box would be pretty.

00:02:57.360 --> 00:03:00.420
Yes, that's right. Because girls also take a lot of pictures.

00:03:01.480 --> 00:03:03.093
Very nice.

00:03:03.093 --> 00:03:06.633
I am so excited. Oh my gosh.

00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:09.300
 I need to buy a bike. 

00:03:09.460 --> 00:03:13.220
My previous one got too old, so I threw it away.

00:03:13.380 --> 00:03:17.400
When I was little, I was jealous of friends who could ride with both hands off the handle bars. 

00:03:17.640 --> 00:03:18.260
Like this? Oh no.

00:03:19.960 --> 00:03:26.960
I wanted to do it like them, and I could let go with one hand, but I could never do two hands. 

00:03:27.320 --> 00:03:29.320
You have to balance well. 

00:03:30.160 --> 00:03:34.640
Balance...oh, well, this is difficult. This bike seems difficult to balance.

00:03:34.960 --> 00:03:39.380
My friends who could ride a bike with two hands off would brag a lot to me.

00:03:40.934 --> 00:03:43.894
Back then, when I was little, (kids) used to brag about even the smallest things.

00:03:44.860 --> 00:03:50.700
Right now, Seokjin and Kyung-hwa went really far away while concentrating on talking. 

00:03:51.040 --> 00:03:56.320
I think they must be absorbed in talking without even noticing that I've escaped in the middle of the ride. 

00:03:56.320 --> 00:03:58.320
The scenery is here so good.

00:03:58.320 --> 00:04:04.600
The weather is not good today, but the scenery that I can see here is good, so I've stopped for a moment.

